solution: class Solution {
public:
    long long mostPoints(vector<vector<int>>& questions) {
        int n = questions.size();
        vector<long long> dp(n + 1, 0);
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
            int points = questions[i][0];
            int brainpower = questions[i][1];
            int next = min(i + brainpower + 1, n);
            dp[i] = max(dp[i + 1], points + dp[next]);
        }
        return dp[0];
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Bottom-up DP scans once from right to left, storing the best score reachable from each index. Each state chooses either skip (carry dp[i+1]) or solve (add points and jump past brainpower questions). Uses O(n) memory; can be reduced to O(1) with rolling variables but kept for clarity.

